n a regular honeycomb lattice is always greater than\nthat of two semi-regular archimedean lattices. The effect of selective site\ndilution of the mixed-spin Ising model on a honeycomb lattice upon phase\ndiagrams is examined. The review affords a brief account of the Ising models\nsolved within MF, EF and exact methods along with a few comments on their\nfuture applicability.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 10 Nov 2015 09:27:55 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 11 Nov 2015 09:50:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-11-12"}
